 Fourteen schools across Lagos State will be jostling for honours at the 13th Olaniyan Basketball Competition, which dunks off on Monday February 17 to 19 at Victory Grammar School, Ikeja. Among the participating teams are Command Secondary School, Ikeja Cantonment; Airforce Secondary, Ikeja; St Theresa Secondary School; Vivian Fowler School, and host – Victory Grammar School. According to the sponsor of the tournament, Chief Christian Francis Olaniyan, the aim is to encourage healthy rivalry among the students as well as unearth talents for the country. He said: “There are lot of prizes to be won apart from the overall winners walking home with giant trophies, other schools that perform well in the competition will cart away prizes and certificates.